00:45:02,784 --> 00:45:06,997
This case went from a who-gives-a-fuck
drug murder to straight-up red ball.

709
00:45:11,126 --> 00:45:13,628
Fuck, I should've picked up that phone.

710
00:45:17,299 --> 00:45:20,552
Hey, sarge. My boy's a witness.
Drug case pending in part 18.

711
00:45:20,635 --> 00:45:22,888
You know for sure he's
killed for that reason?

712
00:45:22,971 --> 00:45:24,055
Don't know shit.

713
00:45:24,139 --> 00:45:26,951
But from the look of the court computer,
this guy's the state's whole case.

714
00:45:26,975 --> 00:45:28,977
Don't put it in the 24
that the guy was a witness.

715
00:45:29,644 --> 00:45:32,814
Trust me, we do not wanna
kick shit in an election year.

716
00:45:33,023 --> 00:45:34,524
Work the case, take the ot,

717
00:45:34,608 --> 00:45:37,277
but Bury the witness angle
till we know for sure.

718
00:45:39,487 --> 00:45:41,072
And close the door.

719
00:45:56,338 --> 00:45:57,589
Yeah.

720
00:45:57,672 --> 00:45:59,299
It's landsman. Homicide.

721
00:45:59,382 --> 00:46:01,384
Is the major in this morning?

722
00:46:02,093 --> 00:46:03,887
Next order of business, class rules.

723
00:46:03,970 --> 00:46:07,933
It helps if the team is constant on these.
Less wiggle room for the children.

724
00:46:08,016 --> 00:46:11,102
- Mrs. Scott?
- Same as last year, double space.

725
00:46:11,186 --> 00:46:13,563
Language arts.
We grade a lot of papers.

726
00:46:13,647 --> 00:46:16,441
It doesn't make them write any better,
but it saves my eyesight.

727
00:46:16,524 --> 00:46:17,984
Demonstrate it for them.

728
00:46:18,068 --> 00:46:21,112
Some of them think double space
means more space between words.

729
00:46:21,196 --> 00:46:24,699
- I'd have thought by eighth grade...
- Rule of thumb here, Mr. Pryzbylewski,

730
00:46:24,783 --> 00:46:25,867
never assume.

731
00:46:25,951 --> 00:46:29,454
Explain what you want them to do,
have them do it, then explain again.

732
00:46:29,537 --> 00:46:31,748
With time and Patience, they'll get it.

733
00:46:31,831 --> 00:46:34,793
- Mrs. Shapiro?
- It's easier to keep track of lab work

734
00:46:34,876 --> 00:46:36,795
if we all use the same heading.

735
00:46:36,878 --> 00:46:39,297
Upper right-hand corner,
above the first blue line,

736
00:46:39,381 --> 00:46:42,968
name, date, and class
number, in that order?

737
00:46:43,051 --> 00:46:45,637
Mr. Pryzbylewski, do you have
anything you want addressed?

738
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:48,139
Can we have them not chew gum?

739
00:46:48,223 --> 00:46:50,141
They won't do it in Ms. Sampson's class,

740
00:46:50,225 --> 00:46:52,644
but in four years,
I have not been able to stop them.

741
00:46:52,727 --> 00:46:55,647
You can try, but first year,
it's best to stick with basics.

742
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:58,942
In team rules, we can only go
with what we can all enforce.

743
00:46:59,192 --> 00:47:01,569
Also, keep your windows closed.

744
00:47:01,653 --> 00:47:03,655
Makes them drowsy, and drowsy's good.

745
00:47:04,406 --> 00:47:06,741
There's a lot to learn. But for now,

746
00:47:06,825 --> 00:47:09,995
build in lots of activities in your
lesson plan, you can't have enough.

747
00:47:10,078 --> 00:47:13,081
You keep them busy,
you keep them off-guard.

748
00:47:16,668 --> 00:47:18,753
You need soft eyes.

749
00:47:19,838 --> 00:47:21,172
Excuse me?

750
00:47:24,592 --> 00:47:28,054
Yeah, but that doesn't prevent you
from giving more under your wife's name,

751
00:47:28,138 --> 00:47:31,516
your children, if they got
separate accounts, yeah.

752
00:47:32,934 --> 00:47:35,687
Sorry, Richie,
can you hold a moment?

753
00:47:35,770 --> 00:47:38,898
Your buddy from the fop.
And he says it's important.

754
00:47:38,982 --> 00:47:41,026
Hey, Stan.

755
00:47:41,109 --> 00:47:43,695
I'm a little busy losing an election here.

756
00:47:43,778 --> 00:47:45,864
You remember about six months ago,

757
00:47:45,947 --> 00:47:49,200
you told me to keep an eye
for any witnesses gettin' clipped?

758
00:47:49,284 --> 00:47:50,952
You remember that?

759
00:47:52,912 --> 00:47:55,040
Who's better than me, Tommy?

760
00:47:57,292 --> 00:47:59,711
Hey, Richie, can I call you back?

761
00:47:59,794 --> 00:48:01,129
Thanks.

762
00:48:06,342 --> 00:48:08,595
Anything else you want me to do,
miss Donnelly?

763
00:48:10,305 --> 00:48:13,683
- You live near duquan weems, correct?
- Dukie?

764
00:48:14,309 --> 00:48:18,021
- I want you to take this to his house.
- Them clothes won't stay clean long.

765
00:48:18,104 --> 00:48:21,566
Make sure you deliver them just to duquan,
not any of the adults in the house,

766
00:48:21,649 --> 00:48:23,777
- just duquan.
- Want me to do it tonight?

767
00:48:23,860 --> 00:48:26,237
That would be great.
And, crystal, thanks for today.

768
00:48:26,321 --> 00:48:29,074
You're welcome, miss Donnelly.

769
00:48:29,157 --> 00:48:30,617
- Can I help you?
- Yes, ma'am.

770
00:48:30,700 --> 00:48:32,911
This young man has to be
registered for school.

771
00:48:32,994 --> 00:48:35,580
- Does he attend here?
- He should.

772
00:48:35,663 --> 00:48:38,625
What I mean is, what grade
were you in last year, dear?

773
00:48:40,585 --> 00:48:42,545
He kinda lost his way some time ago.

774
00:48:42,629 --> 00:48:44,089
He's livin' with me now.

775
00:48:44,172 --> 00:48:47,217
- And you are his...
- Uncle. I'm his uncle.

776
00:48:48,510 --> 00:48:49,761
Come into my office.

777
00:48:57,519 --> 00:48:59,354
Thank you. Excuse me.

778
00:49:03,358 --> 00:49:05,026
To your right. To your right.

779
00:49:05,735 --> 00:49:07,112
One, two, one, two.

780
00:49:07,195 --> 00:49:08,571
One, two, yeah.

781
00:49:16,871 --> 00:49:18,706
Yo, look at coach workin' it, yo.

782
00:49:21,668 --> 00:49:22,794
All right!

783
00:49:22,877 --> 00:49:26,172
All right, man, break.
That's what I like to see, baby.

784
00:49:26,256 --> 00:49:28,133
You gotta use that left a little more.

785
00:49:28,216 --> 00:49:31,803
- Yo, man, you finished?
- Got another two minutes.

786
00:49:31,886 --> 00:49:34,305
Fuck that, I got a fight coming up.
You can come back later.

787
00:49:34,389 --> 00:49:37,016
- Man said he got one more round.
- Step aside, young'UN.

788
00:49:37,100 --> 00:49:39,811
Naw, man, bag is mine
for four rounds and I only did three.

789
00:49:39,894 --> 00:49:42,147
- Fuck that.
- Yo.

790
00:49:42,230 --> 00:49:43,940
What the fuck you tryin' to prove, huh?

791
00:49:44,023 --> 00:49:46,442
Come on, man, come on.
What's going on, boy?

792
00:49:46,526 --> 00:49:48,712
I got a fight Saturday,
an' the boy won't get off the bag.

793
00:49:48,736 --> 00:49:52,740
What the fuck he on the bag for anyway?
He don't even fight. He don't even spar.

794
00:49:52,824 --> 00:49:55,702
- Spar with your ass any day.
- Come on, then.

795
00:49:55,785 --> 00:49:59,330
Y'all be cool, you hear me?
I ain't putting up with this foolishness.

796
00:49:59,414 --> 00:50:01,833
Come here, Michael.

797
00:50:01,916 --> 00:50:04,586
- I can work the bag now, right?
- Not yet. Just wait.

798
00:50:04,669 --> 00:50:06,921
- You said four rounds.
- Yeah, I know what I said.

799
00:50:07,380 --> 00:50:10,341
You finish up your rounds,
and then Justin gets on.

800
00:50:10,425 --> 00:50:12,385
I don't want hear no more street talk.

801
00:50:12,468 --> 00:50:14,068
We boxin' up in here, we ain't fightin'.

802
00:50:14,137 --> 00:50:16,347
He wanna get in the ring with me,

803
00:50:16,431 --> 00:50:19,726
- we can go.
- Look here, let me tell you something.

804
00:50:19,809 --> 00:50:22,020
You can come here, work out,
use the equipment.

805
00:50:22,103 --> 00:50:25,190
But nobody gets in that ring
unless they're being trained.

806
00:50:25,273 --> 00:50:27,275
You wanna be trained?

807
00:50:28,484 --> 00:50:30,195
I've been watching you hit that bag.

808
00:50:30,445 --> 00:50:34,365
You got a natural right hand,
the way you throw it, the way you land it.

809
00:50:34,449 --> 00:50:36,993
Now, if I was to train you,
we'd have to start with floor work.

810
00:50:37,076 --> 00:50:41,706
'Cause see, if you don't know how to move,
you ain't got no business being in that ring.

811
00:50:41,789 --> 00:50:43,458
So what you think?

812
00:50:43,541 --> 00:50:45,460
I'd train you myself, personally.

813
00:50:48,671 --> 00:50:52,050
Nah, really, I just wanna keep doing
what I been doing.

814
00:50:52,133 --> 00:50:53,509
All right.

815
00:51:00,141 --> 00:51:02,393
Let's see that right. Uh-huh.

816
00:51:16,324 --> 00:51:18,117
Is dukie here?

817
00:51:18,201 --> 00:51:20,995
What's that? That's for duquan, right?

818
00:51:21,079 --> 00:51:22,705
I take it to him.

819
00:51:23,706 --> 00:51:25,124
Gimme.

820
00:51:25,208 --> 00:51:27,460
Hey, crystal.

821
00:51:27,543 --> 00:51:29,545
Miss Donnelly said to give you these.

822
00:51:29,629 --> 00:51:31,339
Ok. I'll be right down.

823
00:51:33,758 --> 00:51:35,176
What?

824
00:51:36,427 --> 00:51:38,263
And for either of my opponents to suggest

825
00:51:38,346 --> 00:51:42,934
that downtown development comes
at the expense of our city's neighborhoods,

826
00:51:43,017 --> 00:51:47,063
well, that's just unfair and divisive.

827
00:51:47,146 --> 00:51:50,191
For them to suggest
that my administration

828
00:51:50,275 --> 00:51:53,278
has not been responsive, well...

829
00:51:53,361 --> 00:51:55,780
Economic development
cannot be a band-aid.

830
00:51:55,863 --> 00:51:59,492
It is a long-term process
that requires commitment

831
00:51:59,575 --> 00:52:02,453
to retraining our workforce
and, as I said before,

832
00:52:02,537 --> 00:52:05,415
this can only be successful
in a city where people feel safe.

833
00:52:05,498 --> 00:52:09,127
So before we can begin to think
about luring new industries to Baltimore,

834
00:52:09,210 --> 00:52:11,629
we need to think about
how we can make these neighborhoods

835
00:52:11,713 --> 00:52:13,965
and this city safe once again.

836
00:52:14,048 --> 00:52:18,386
Mr. Carcetti may think it's in his
interests to exploit people's fears.

837
00:52:18,469 --> 00:52:21,889
He's been doing it
throughout this campaign.

838
00:52:21,973 --> 00:52:25,143
I'm offended by it,
personally. But the fact is,

839
00:52:25,226 --> 00:52:28,730
that violent crime is down city-wide,

840
00:52:28,813 --> 00:52:32,692
and our police department
is working hard to keep it that way,

841
00:52:32,775 --> 00:52:35,737
and will continue to do so
under my administration.

842
00:52:35,820 --> 00:52:38,781
Councilman carcetti,
you have two minutes to respond.

843
00:52:39,157 --> 00:52:42,785
Does anyone in this room really believe
that crime is down in Baltimore?

844
00:52:42,869 --> 00:52:44,162
You calling me a liar, Tommy?

845
00:52:44,245 --> 00:52:46,456
Gentleman, please.
No personal interactions.

846
00:52:46,539 --> 00:52:49,334
- Councilman carcetti.
- Can the mayor honestly tell

847
00:52:49,417 --> 00:52:51,836
the people of rosemont,
of belair Edison,

848
00:52:51,919 --> 00:52:56,090
of highlandtown or cherry hill
there's less drug-dealing, less violence?

849
00:52:56,341 --> 00:52:58,551
Any statistics coming
from the police department

850
00:52:58,634 --> 00:53:02,180
cannot be trusted, because under this
mayor, the police are more concerned

851
00:53:02,263 --> 00:53:05,433
with protecting Clarence Royce politically
than fighting crime.

852
00:53:05,767 --> 00:53:08,436
There's no leadership
and morale has never been lower.

853
00:53:08,519 --> 00:53:09,729
I'll change that.

854
00:53:09,812 --> 00:53:12,106
It's business as usual down at city hall

855
00:53:12,190 --> 00:53:14,609
and as a result, our response to crime

856
00:53:14,692 --> 00:53:17,153
has been characterized time and time again

857
00:53:17,236 --> 00:53:19,614
by wanton indifference.

858
00:53:19,697 --> 00:53:21,074
32 yards!

859
00:53:21,157 --> 00:53:24,452
What do I mean by business as usual?

860
00:53:24,535 --> 00:53:26,704
What do I mean by wanton indifference?

861
00:53:26,788 --> 00:53:31,125
Well, last night
in west Baltimore, on lanvale street,

862
00:53:31,209 --> 00:53:33,753
another citizen was shot and killed.

863
00:53:33,836 --> 00:53:37,548
This victim was a key witness in a
drug case that had yet to come to court.

864
00:53:37,632 --> 00:53:40,718
Courageously, this
man had agreed to testify

865
00:53:40,802 --> 00:53:42,512
in two weeks' time in that case.

866
00:53:42,595 --> 00:53:46,766
The police should have been protecting him.
They were not, and he was murdered.

867
00:53:47,725 --> 00:53:49,519
- Oh, shit.
- Why? Because this mayor...

868
00:53:49,602 --> 00:53:53,523
- You're prime-time, Eddie.
- ..Would not spend the money to protect him.

869
00:53:53,606 --> 00:53:55,441
Now I have no doubt
that in a moment or two

870
00:53:55,525 --> 00:53:58,444
Clarence Royce will accuse me
of exploiting this man's death

871
00:53:58,528 --> 00:54:03,199
for my own political purpose,
but the truth is, a year ago

872
00:54:03,282 --> 00:54:06,327
I wrote the mayor a letter.
I have copies for anyone who wants one.

873
00:54:06,411 --> 00:54:10,415
I begged him to spend the money
and make witness protection a priority.

874
00:54:10,498 --> 00:54:11,582
He ignored me.

875
00:54:12,041 --> 00:54:15,420
I even teamed up with our legislative
leaders, delegate Watkins and others,

876
00:54:15,503 --> 00:54:18,589
to get matching funds for witness
protection approved in Annapolis.

877
00:54:18,673 --> 00:54:20,800
And incredibly those matching funds

878
00:54:20,883 --> 00:54:22,718
were never claimed by this administration.

879
00:54:22,802 --> 00:54:25,096
Now to mention this now may be exploitive,

880
00:54:25,179 --> 00:54:27,557
I don't know, I only know it's true,

881
00:54:27,640 --> 00:54:30,560
and on such truths I
ask the voters of our city

882
00:54:30,643 --> 00:54:32,979
to consider a change.

883
00:54:36,941 --> 00:54:41,279
Folks, please, hold your applause
until after the round of questions is over.

884
00:54:41,362 --> 00:54:42,488
Mayor Royce?

885
00:54:42,613 --> 00:54:44,991
No more surprises, huh?

886
00:54:45,950 --> 00:54:49,579
I am unaware of the specifics
of the incident

887
00:54:49,662 --> 00:54:51,664
to which councilman carcetti is referring,

888
00:54:52,498 --> 00:54:55,251
so I can't answer that directly,

889
00:54:55,334 --> 00:55:01,174
however, I can say
that this city places the highest priority

890
00:55:01,257 --> 00:55:04,260
on protecting those citizens
who come foward to testify,

891
00:55:04,343 --> 00:55:07,180
and we will continue to do so.

892
00:55:07,263 --> 00:55:11,184
Mr. Carcetti states that he wrote a letter

893
00:55:11,267 --> 00:55:14,270
expressing his concerns,
and I'm sure that he did.

894
00:55:14,353 --> 00:55:17,064
I mean, it's easy enough to write letters

895
00:55:17,148 --> 00:55:19,734
when all you have to do is write letters.

896
00:55:20,109 --> 00:55:23,112
But when you are required

897
00:55:23,196 --> 00:55:25,740
to run a city

898
00:55:25,823 --> 00:55:28,576
on limited resources,

899
00:55:28,659 --> 00:55:30,912
and balance priorities,

900
00:55:30,995 --> 00:55:33,831
well, then... well, then you understand

901
00:55:33,915 --> 00:55:38,085
that writing letters
will not solve the problem, oh, no.

902
00:55:39,921 --> 00:55:41,881
Shit, girl.

903
00:55:42,340 --> 00:55:44,675
You know I'm-a roll wit' you.

904
00:55:46,260 --> 00:55:48,179
I need some kinda break.

905
00:55:49,597 --> 00:55:51,265
Mm-hm.

906
00:56:06,614 --> 00:56:08,824
Oh, shit.

907
00:56:21,379 --> 00:56:26,300
Ain't nothin' worse than them bitches with
fucked-up nails at the Blackjack table.

908
00:56:27,468 --> 00:56:28,928
You know.

909
00:56:30,388 --> 00:56:31,973
Hold on.

910
00:56:32,890 --> 00:56:36,269
You think my son ain't gonna go up
to that school lookin' like himself?

911
00:56:42,692 --> 00:56:44,485
I don't believe we can
get a handle on crime

912
00:56:44,569 --> 00:56:46,612
until we get a handle on the schools.

913
00:56:46,696 --> 00:56:48,781
Because we need to be
thinking about these kids

914
00:56:48,864 --> 00:56:50,825
before the corners take them.

915
00:56:50,908 --> 00:56:53,202
And this means a renewed focus
on our schools...

916
00:57:00,835 --> 00:57:02,003
Oh!

